# gated access list - BLACKLIST by IP / CIDR.
#
# One entry per line: a single IP (v4 or v6) or a CIDR range. Blank
# lines and text after '#' are ignored. Drop as many *.ips files here
# as you like (e.g. abusers.ips, badnets.ips).
#
# A blacklisted client is blocked outright (403), UNLESS it is also in
# the whitelist (the whitelist always wins). Files are hot-reloaded.
#
# Examples (commented out — nothing is blocked by default):
# 192.0.2.66
# 198.51.100.0/24
# 2001:db8:dead::/48
